# Design System Overview

This design system organizes components by complexity into a single components directory:

- **Basic Components**: UI elements like buttons, inputs, selects
- **Complex Components**: More advanced UI patterns like cards, tabs, banners

## Key Directories
- `components/`: All UI components like [buttons.css](mdc:components/buttons.css), [text-input.css](mdc:components/text-input.css), [select.css](mdc:components/select.css), and [card.css](mdc:components/card.css)
- `styles/`: Core styling utilities including [tokens.css](mdc:styles/tokens.css) for design tokens
- `examples/`: Implementation examples of components

## Implementation Guidelines
1. Use existing components when possible
2. Follow the established naming conventions
3. Maintain consistent spacing using CSS variables (`var(--space-*)`)
4. Use the defined color tokens (`var(--neutral-*)`, `var(--success-*)`, etc.)
5. Structure components based on complexity and purpose
